          "[Sequence of Encoded LWA scores]",
          "After 5 LWA",
          "The authors divide the assessments based on sequential distribution - across course duration.\n\nFor each quartile of course duration the authors extract perform feature generation based on the distribution - guided by the median and quartiles of the assessments.\n\nThese are subsequently encoded into 4 states: \n\nA - Non-attempters, \nB - 0 to Q1\nC - Q1 to Med\nD - Med or greater ",
          "seqHMM,\nSVM, RF, Logistic Regression, MLP",
          "Holdout Method",
          "{Accuracy: [0.8767, 0.9340], Precision: [0.8571, 0.9464], Recall: [0.8854, 0.9924], F1-Score: [0.905, 0.938], Cohen’s Kappa: [0.719, 0.886]}",
          "Authors do a study using Hidden Markov Models. \n\nThe authors use this approach and compare it against other baselines. HMM perform at a comparative level (and sometimes better) than baselines.",
          "- Does not consider multiple institutions.\n\n- No use of other data sources.\n\n- Does not allow prediction of assessment performance."
